    "body": "Hi @WardenJakx, we validate these values like that because that's how [the spec](https://ethereum.github.io/execution-apis/api-documentation/) specifies storage slots:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/assets/417134/747286d4-4f73-4aee-8a6e-4e4e6d5047d5)\r\n\r\nWhat you can do is use [our `setStorageAt` network helper](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-network-helpers/docs/reference#setstorageat(address,-index,-value)) which should abstract you from this validation.\r\n\r\nTentatively closing this, but happy to re-open if I'm missing something here.",
